## Running tests

```bash
make check    # full suite with branch coverage
```

To run tests alone without the full gate: `uv run pytest` (or `cd {{ component_dir }} && uv run pytest` for component layout).

## Layout

```
tests/
  conftest.py       # shared fixtures
  test_imports.py   # architectural boundary enforcement
  unit/             # pure logic, no I/O
  integration/      # real I/O (db, filesystem, network)
```

Keep unit tests fast and free of I/O. Integration tests may use real databases, real files, or real HTTP — never mocks of those boundaries.

## Dependency-direction tests

`tests/test_imports.py` enforces import boundaries via AST analysis. Populate the `BOUNDARIES` list with one entry per architectural boundary:

```python
BOUNDARIES: list[tuple[str, str]] = [
    ("db", "{{ package_name }}.cli"),   # db must not import from cli
    ("db", "{{ package_name }}.api"),   # db must not import from api
]
```

Each entry is `(source_layer, forbidden_import_prefix)`. A single parametrized test covers all of them.

## Fixtures

- Define fixtures in `conftest.py` at the appropriate scope (root for shared, subdirectory for local).
- Prefer function scope. Use session scope only for expensive, genuinely read-only resources.

## Coverage

Target: branch coverage over `{{ src_root }}/{{ package_name }}`. Config is in `pyproject.toml`. HTML report lands in `htmlcov/` after `make check`.

Exclude deliberately unreachable branches with `# pragma: no cover`.
